<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF82EF41FF42FEDBFDFBFDA0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF82EF41FF42FEDBFCF7FE4C" blockId="42.[151,1437,257,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF82EF41FF42FEDBFEE7FE30" bold="true" box="[199,338,366,392]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Comments:</emphasis>
This species presents a very broad geographic distribution, and has four junior synonyms, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF82EF41FACAFEDAFE1CFE15" authority="(Walker, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Pycnopalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contaminata">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF82EF41FACAFEDAFF4EFE14" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">P. contaminata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF82EF41FE8DFE27FE17FE15" author="Walker, F." box="[264,418,402,429]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref37090" refString="Walker, F. (1869) Catalogue of the specimens of Dermaptera Saltatoria in the collection of the British Museum. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 218 pp." type="book" year="1869">Walker, 1869</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF82EF41FE31FE26FD0BFE14" authority="Vignon, 1930" authorityName="Vignon" authorityYear="1930" box="[436,702,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Pycnopalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morata">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF82EF41FE31FE26FDAAFE14" box="[436,543,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">P. morata</emphasis>
Vignon, 1930
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF82EF41FD4DFE26FC5CFE14" authority="Rehn, 1903" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1903" box="[712,1001,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Pycnopalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mortuifolia">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF82EF41FD4DFE26FCD5FE14" box="[712,864,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">P. mortuifolia</emphasis>
Rehn, 1903
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF82EF41FBA5FE26FAD2FE14" authority="Vignon, 1930" authorityName="Vignon" authorityYear="1930" box="[1056,1383,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Pycnopalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="permaculata">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF82EF41FBA5FE26FB7CFE14" box="[1056,1225,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">P. permaculata</emphasis>
Vignon, 1930
</taxonomicName>
. The individuals present a remarkable tegmina morphology, with a necrotic area well delimited, besides the conspicuous pronotum, where two stains that resembles a heart are found.
</paragraph>
